      • doTableModificationComplete

        protected static void doTableModificationComplete​(CcddMain main,
                                                  CcddClassesDataTable.TableInformation tableInfo,
                                                  java.util.List<CcddClassesDataTable.TableModification> modifications,
                                                  java.util.List<CcddClassesDataTable.TableModification> deletions,
                                                  boolean forceUpdate,
                                                  boolean isRefFieldChange,
                                                  boolean isMsgNameIDChange)
        Perform the steps needed following execution of a table modification. This includes closing child table editors that are no longer valid and modifying child tables when a prototype table is changed
        Parameters:
        main - reference to CcddMain
        tableInfo - table information
        modifications - list of row update information
        deletions - list of row deletion information
        forceUpdate - true to make the changes to other tables (e.g., following a data type or macro change); false to only make changes to tables other than the one in which the changes originally took place
        isRefFieldChange - true is a data field has a variable (command, message name and ID) reference input type
        isMsgNameIDChange - true is a message name or ID changed and a cell or field uses the message name and ID input type

      • updateTableNames

        protected static void updateTableNames​(CcddMain main,
                                       java.lang.String oldPrototype,
                                       java.lang.String newPrototype,
                                       java.lang.String oldVariableName,
                                       java.lang.String newVariableName,
                                       CcddTableEditorDialog editorDialog,
                                       CcddTableEditorHandler editor)
        Update the table name, editor dialog tab, and editor dialog frame when the prototype name (data type for a structure table) or the variable name for a structure type table is changed
        Parameters:
        main - reference to CcddMain
        oldPrototype - original prototype name (same as the data type for a structure table)
        newPrototype - current prototype name (same as the data type for a structure table)
        oldVariableName - original variable name if this change is for a structure table
        newVariableName - current variable name if this change is for a structure table
        editorDialog - current editor dialog to which the changes are compared
        editor - current editor to which the changes are compared
